1. The chosen letter is often a repeat submission from a regular contributor.
2. The chosen letter may not be the best or most representative of the submissions.
3. The editorial riposte is sometimes written in response to a previous letter from the same contributor.
4. The chosen letter may not be representative of the overall sentiment of the submissions.
5. The chosen letter may be selected based on factors other than its content or quality.
6. The chosen letter may be chosen by a different person or department within the newspaper.
7. The chosen letter may not be chosen at all, but rather be a predetermined piece written by the newspaper staff.